ceiling

SortedList<E> ceiling(E e)
Returns a view of the portion of this list containing the least elements which are greater than or equal to the given element, or null if no such elements exist. This implies that if this list does not contain duplicate elements this method will return a list containing only a single element or null if no match can be made.

Parameters:
e - the element to match
Returns:
the least elements greater than or equal to e, or null if there is no such elements

headList

SortedList<E> headList(E toElement,
                       boolean inclusive)
Returns a view of the portion of this list whose elements are less than (or equal to, if inclusive is true) toElement. This implies that if the list contains duplicate elements and inclusive is true, all of the elements which are equal to toElement will be included in the returned list. The returned list is backed by this list, so changes in the returned list are reflected in this list.

Parameters:
toElement - high endpoint (exclusive) of the returned list
inclusive - true if the high endpoint is to be included in the returned view
Returns:
a view of the portion of this list whose elements are strictly less than toElement
Throws:
ClassCastException - if toElement is not comparable to the elements in this list
NullPointerException - if toElement is null and this list does not permit null elements

subList

SortedList<E> subList(E fromElement,
                      boolean fromInclusive,
                      E toElement,
                      boolean toInclusive)
Returns a view of the portion of this list whose elements range from fromElement to toElement. If fromElement and toElement are equal, the returned list is empty unless fromInclusive and toInclusive are both true. The returned list is backed by this list, so changes in the returned list are reflected in this list.

Parameters:
fromElement - low endpoint (inclusive) of the returned list
fromInclusive - true if the low endpoint is to be included in the returned view
toElement - high endpoint (exclusive) of the returned list
toInclusive - true if the high endpoint is to be included in the returned view
Returns:
a view of the portion of this list whose elements range from fromElement, inclusive, to toElement, exclusive
Throws:
ClassCastException - if fromElement or toElement is not comparable to the elements in this list
NullPointerException - if fromElement or toElement is null and this list does not permit null elements
IllegalArgumentException - if fromElement is greater than toElement

tailList
